&lt;p&gt;You can break news, decipher policy developments, and anticipate where Washington is heading on critical issues that affect markets, companies, and the broader economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can contextualize and humanize complicated policy decisions—writing with urgency, sophistication, and style. A strong grasp of financial policy and corporate regulation is essential, as is an instinct for what matters to DealBook’s business-savvy readers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid position based in Washington, D.C. and includes regular attendance in the office each week per your departmental guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
